<div id="review_698262837" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/698262837" />
    <a title="Darwin8u" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2294090-darwin8u"><img alt="Darwin8u" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1547440402p2/2294090.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/698262837?book_show_action=true">Aug 18, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Darwin8u" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Darwin8u" href="/user/show/2294090-darwin8u">Darwin8u</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2294090-darwin8u?shelf=100-modern-library">100-modern-library</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2294090-darwin8u?shelf=2015">2015</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2294090-darwin8u?shelf=100-mccaffery">100-mccaffery</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer698262837" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15501348529270795923"><i>“How fragile we are under the sheltering sky. Behind the sheltering sky is a vast dark universe, and we&apos;re just so small.”</i> <br/>― Paul Bowles, The Sheltering Sky<br/><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1422318947i/13485396.jpg' width='400' height='300' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>Paul Bowles masterpiece reminds me of some alternate, trippy, version of Fitzgerald&apos;s <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/46164.Tender_Is_the_Night' title='Tender Is the Night by F. Scott Fitzgerald' rel='nofollow noopener'>Tender Is the Night</a>, but instead we see the other side of the Mediterranean. Tangier and the deserts of North Africa take the place of the South of France. A different love triangle exposes different forms of loneliness, madness, love, and existential expats</span>
  <span id="freeText15501348529270795923" style="display:none"><i>“How fragile we are under the sheltering sky. Behind the sheltering sky is a vast dark universe, and we're just so small.”</i> <br>― Paul Bowles, The Sheltering Sky<br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1422318947i/13485396.jpg" width="400" height="300" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Paul Bowles masterpiece reminds me of some alternate, trippy, version of Fitzgerald's <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/46164.Tender_Is_the_Night" title="Tender Is the Night by F. Scott Fitzgerald" rel="nofollow noopener">Tender Is the Night</a>, but instead we see the other side of the Mediterranean. Tangier and the deserts of North Africa take the place of the South of France. A different love triangle exposes different forms of loneliness, madness, love, and existential expats.<br><br>The thing I love about Bowles is he brings a composer's mind to writing. His novel isn't propelled forward by a strong plot (although it has plot) or attractive characters (none of the characters are very attractive), but the music of his language alone pushes and pulls, tugs and compels the reader page after page. It felt very much like I was floating limp and languid in Bowles prose as his hypnotic sentences washed over me and drifted me slowly toward the inevitable end.<br><br>Most days, I don't feel a real need to read a book twice. I might need to make an exception for 'The Sheltering Sky'.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15501348529270795923" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


